args:
The group slays the pernicious pumpkin-headed
fiend, and the Halloween party begins at last.
During the festivities, Althemia questions the
prince as to whether her or Elisanne's costume
is cuter, and Silke teaches a lesson to the
miscreant responsible for the whole fiend affair.
I'd given up hope once that pumpkin-head\nthing appeared.
That big jerk wanted to eat every last one\nof the village's treats.
It almost stole the treat from trick or treat!
I'm glad there was no serious harm done.
And now, I think it's long past time for us\nto celebrate Halloween. I want everyone\nto have a great time at the party!
It was a long road here, but I'm glad we're\nready to go at last.
This is the first party we've thrown since\ncoming to the castle.
I really wanted it to go well.
Heh. Sorry. Was that a little childish?
Not at all. It just set me to thinking about\nhow kind you truly are.
It's when times are really hard—as they\nhave been for us—that people most need\na day of fun to forget their troubles.
I'm happy to hear you say that.
Especially because I think we have a lot of\nhard, sad times ahead of us.
So if we have a great time today, maybe\nit'll make up for what lies ahead.
Then let's make some fine memories\ntogether!
Oh, that reminds me! You were going to\nask me something right before that\npumpkin creature appeared.
Well, now I'm even MORE curious.\nYou know you can tell me anything, right?
No! I mean, I merely... Oh, very well.\nYour Highness, do you—
Hey! I told you, I want to get changed!\nNow leave me alone for ten freaking\nseconds already!
Such things should be taken care of\nBEFORE the party, Madam Althemia.
I TRIED! But then you started ranting about\nhow we were so far behind schedule and\nI couldn't make the time!
I prevented Madam Althemia from exiting\nthe party venue. ...She took it poorly.
Regardless, I cannot permit people to miss\nthe event my master has so longed for.
Do you not like the party, Althemia?
The party isn't the issue—I just want to\nchange out of this outfit.
I look like a total weirdo, and everyone\nkeeps staring at me!
I assure you that no one in this castle\nthinks such a thing, Madam Althemia.
I mean, maybe people are just impressed\nwith what a cool costume it is.
And Elisanne's costume looks cute, too!\nYou did an amazing job, Althemia!
Wh-why would you bring that up?!
I'm just being honest. Edward's looks\nquite dashing, too.
I have nothing but respect for what you\ndid. I couldn't begin to craft something\nlike that.
Th-thanks... \nUm, can I ask you something,\n{player_name}?
Come on! Aren't you a LITTLE curious?
Well, maybe just a... Er, I mean, no!
The whole point of these costumes was for\nus to wear them in BATTLE!
Madam Elisanne, why do you look\nso worried?
Staring at me like that isn't going to help!\nOkay, let's seeeee...
Give us treats or we're gonna play a trick\non you!
Uh oh. Outta goodies, are ya?\nWell then, it's a trick for you!
Uwaaah! S-stop, Ranzal...\nAAAH HA HA HA! N-no more!
AAAAH HA HA HA! S-stop... HA HA HA!
Oh, dear. It looks like I'm too late.\nWell, let me give you three some treats,\njust in case.
If you get caught up with those two and\ntheir little games, just hand them one of\nthese and... Mmm?
C-Cleo? Why are you...staring at me?
Oh wow! Elly and Althemia's faces are\nSUPER red!
Did something happen to you two?
...Rrr! How annoying! I can't BELIEVE\nthey found that magic sigil.
It's fine, though. I'll simply draw another\none and then... BWAH?!
YOU! Do you have ANY idea how expensive\nthis...ink...was...?
You made a mess of my dress.
Er, h-hold on, now! Let's not be hasty!
Now I have even more laundry to do.\n...Hmph!
